 index starts from 0  
 name="lakshman"
 name[0]   'l'
 name[20]   index error
 name[-1]  'n'
  index support positive and negitive
  name[-100]   index out of range error


  slice operator

  name="lakshman"
  name[0:]     lakshman
  syntax : [start:stop]
it returns start and end-1
invalid numbers you enterd it will showing empty string 


positive index left to right
negitive index right to left

     concatenate (+ ) => one is str and one is str internally int with base  10
'name+raja'  ='nameraja'

'anme'+'10'='anme10'

* operator=>it support  one is str and one is int

'name'*3='namenamename'








